definitions.definition: Let $P_{p}^{0}$ be the point such that lines $P_{p}^{0}C$ and $AB$ are parallel (and {\tt PRATIO} $P_{p}^{0}$ $C$ $A$ $B$ $1$).
Let $M_{medc}^{1}$ be the midpoint of the segment $AA1$.
Let $T_{medc}^{2}$ be the point on bisector of the segment $AA1$ (such that {\tt TRATIO} $T_{medc}^{2}$ $M_{medc}^{1}$ $A$ $1$).
Let $F_{norm}^{3}$ be the foot of the normal from the point $A1$ on the line $b$.
Let $F_{norma}^{4}$ be the foot of the normal from the point $B3$ on the line $a$.

NDGcondition.explanation: lines M_{medc}^{1}T_{medc}^{2} and AC are not parallel (construction based assumption)
points A1, A and Care not collinear (foot is not the point itself; construction based assumption)
